---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config/site';
const updated = '2026-06-18';
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`Cookies | ${SITE.name}`}
  description="Aheadcount uses no tracking cookies. Analytics via Cloudflare Web Analytics is cookieless."
>
  <article class="section">
    <div class="container-x prose prose-slate max-w-3xl">
      <h1>Cookie statement</h1>
      <p><em>Last updated: {updated}</em></p>

      <h2>Short version</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>This site uses no tracking cookies.</strong>
        We use <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/web-analytics/">Cloudflare Web Analytics</a> for aggregate visit statistics —
        cookieless and privacy-friendly. That's why you see no cookie banner.
      </p>

      <h2>Full explanation</h2>
      <p>
        Cloudflare Web Analytics measures page views without cookies and without placing an identifiable
        unique-user ID in your browser. No fingerprint or cross-site profile is built. More info:
        <a href="https://developers.cloudflare.com/web-analytics/">developers.cloudflare.com/web-analytics</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        If we ever switch to an analytics system that does require cookies, we'll add a GDPR/ePrivacy-compliant
        cookie banner at that point. That's not on the roadmap today.
      </p>

      <h2>Functional storage</h2>
      <p>
        We use <code>localStorage</code> in your browser for one small thing: if you click a pricing CTA and then sign up,
        we remember which tier you clicked so it can travel with your sign-up. This is not a cookie and the data never leaves your browser.
        The planner demo also computes entirely in your browser — nothing you type into it is sent anywhere.
      </p>

      <h2>Questions?</h2>
      <p>See also our <a href="/privacy/">privacy policy</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
